{
  "doc_id": "46458",
  "text": "Different configurations of the generative models have been assessed by varying the number of hidden states C as follows: C ∈ {6, 8, 10} for the homogenous models, C ∈ {8, 10, 16} for the input-driven IO, and C ∈ {81, 100, 225, 400} for GTM-SD. In addition, for the Glycans tasks, we have also tested smaller state spaces, such as C = 2 and C = 4 for the homogenous and IO models, respectively, and C = 49 for GTM-SD. The number of tested hidden states has been determined following the guidelines in the original paper for the various generative models, such as [CITATION_1] and [CITATION_2] . The AM-GTM kernel is also evaluated with respect to the choice of the neighborhood metaparameter , whose values are allowed to vary in {0.05, 0.1, 0.2}. These values ensure that the AM-GTM neighborhood covers a map area that is comparable with the coverage suggested in [CITATION_3] for the original AM kernel over an SOM-SD map (i.e., about 1% − −2% of the lattice).",
